{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionA well-known side effect of diabetes mellitus called diabetic retinopathy has become a major public health issue since it affects millions of people globally.",
    "If neglected, this progressive eye condition can cause vision loss and finally cause blindness.",
    "Worldwide diabetes incidence is increasing, which emphasizes the need for quick, scalable diabetes early detection and care methods.",
    "In its early stages, diabetic retinopathy is frequently asymptomatic and can be sneaky.",
    "By the time symptoms appear, irreparable harm may have already been done."
  ]
}